---
layout: page
title: "Newsletter"
quote: "The internet’s weirdest smart stories, curated by a human. One high-signal email per month."
---

<div>
    <div class="md:grid md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-8 items-start">
        <div>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold pb-4 dark:text-savjeewhite">High-signal science & tech, once a month.</h2>
            <p class="prose dark:prose-dark">
                The internet’s weirdest smart stories — curated by a human.
                <br>No AI slop. No spam. Just one monthly email with the most interesting science, tech, and nerdy finds worth your time.
            </p>

            <ul class="mt-6 space-y-2 dark:text-savjeewhite">
                <li>✅ Humanly curated (AI helps with discovery, not copy-paste)</li>
                <li>✅ 5-minute entertaining read, one email per month</li>
                <li>✅ Cool stories and other nerdy finds</li>
            </ul>

            <p class="pt-6 text-savjeelightgrey3 dark:text-savjeelightgrey3">Published since 2021 • 60+ editions shipped</p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-6 md:mt-0">
            {% render "components/newsletter-box.html", noDescription: true %}
        </div>
    </div>

    {% assign newslettersByYear = collections.newsletter | groupByYear %}
    {% for yearObj in newslettersByYear reversed %}
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold pb-4 pt-16 dark:text-savjeewhite">{{ yearObj.year }}</h3>

        {% for newsletter in yearObj.posts reversed %}
            <div class="py-3 leading-tight border-b border-b-savjeelightgrey4 last:border-none">
                <a href="{{newsletter.url}}" class="no-underline hover:underline">{{newsletter.data.title}}</a><br>
                <span class="text-savjeelightgrey3 text-sm">Sent on {{newsletter.date | date: "%B %e, %Y" }}</span>
            </div>
        {% endfor %}
    {% endfor %}
</div>